post_text: Yesterday's assembly by KC WOLF was really nice. He had a great no bullying program for the elementary and a life lesson program for the high school side. I hope everyone enjoyed it.
text: Yesterday's assembly by KC WOLF was really nice. He had a great no bullying program for the elementary and a life lesson program for the high school side. I hope everyone enjoyed it.

post_text:
We have had fun filling some of the voids that we needed at the school. So far we have purchased 2 new microwaves to speed along our youths lunches, We have purchased 5 new benches for the gathering point on the playground, 3 more benches to spread out around the playground in shady spots, We are funding 1/2 of the no bullying program that will be held next week for all students (this we split with FCA), we purchased shirts for all employees in the health and wellness program and have orderd shirts for the high school teachers ,etc for the no bullying program.
This what your participation in PTSO fundraisers allows us to doand for that we thank you....
Your PTSO Board members, Deb Duncan, Emily Baker, Christl Brownlee, Renee Baker and me......

Wow! All I can say is just wow. What a great time last night. The new year is off to a great start. We had a great turnout for the hot dogs and snowcones. Many many thanks to Jim Neuenschwander for bringing his big cooker once again. Nothing like a hot dog cooked on the grill. Thanks to all the other volunteers who served, helped set up and clean up. You know who you are and i hope you know how much you are appreciated. I also wanted to thank John, Braxton and Nevaeh for totally handling the snow cone table. Not bad for 5th and 6th graders. Seems hard to believe they are so old already.
I really enjoyed seeing so many sitting in the cafeteria and catching up after the summer break. Thats why we do this. Lets keep the good feelings going throughout the whole school year.

PTSO is proud to announce that A Small World Gift workshop has arrived. It will be available to students starting December 3rd and it will go until December 15th.

A small world gift shop is a place where the kids can buy inexpensive high quality gifts for friends and family. 99% of the items are under the cost of $6. Flyers will be going home tomorrow.

post_text: IT'S THE FINAL COUNTDOWN!! School starts in 15 days! Are you thinking about what the 2015-2016 school year will bring for your children? How about ways you can get involved and improve the educational experience? The Lakeland PTSO has already started brainstorming for the new school year! We are excited to announce new themes, ideas, and opportunities! Stay tuned for announcements on the great events this year and how you can become a member.
